text: A venue equipped for conferences and workshops.

Recently, the building management banned bicycle parking in unused and out-of-sight areas outside the building. Employees are now forced to park in an open, unsecured area where locking bicycles is impossible. The location is also on a slope and without proper support, making it difficult to keep bikes upright instead of falling on ground, especially in windy conditions. This decision disregards the needs of employees who rely on cycling for their commute and shows how little the management cares about the working class.
No parking within its vicinity. Nearest is macallister multi storey or open air carpark.
Quiet place to have coffee and food. Recommended for visitors who wants a place to chill
